text.section:
The subscribers shall execute in duplicate articles of incorporation and agree to the terms thereof, which articles shall state:
The name, which shall include the words "credit union" and which shall not be the same as that of any other credit union in this state, and the location where the proposed credit union is to have its principal place of business;
That the existence of the credit union shall be perpetual;
The par value of the shares of the credit union; and
The names and addresses of the subscribers to the articles of incorporation, and the number of shares subscribed to by each, which shall be determined by the board.
